\pard\sa160\sb120\b\fs26 Appendix A: Specification Document\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 The following appendix reproduces the project constitution and specification from `dvrs-web-app-design.md`.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa180\qc\b\fs32 DVRS In-Band Planning Web App\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa160\sb120\b\fs26 1. Constitution\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 1.1 Purpose\b0\par
\pard\sa120 Build a web-based application that helps a public-safety radio planner evaluate Motorola Solutions DVR-LX 700 MHz and 800 MHz standard in-band configurations from minimal user input, then present:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? technically valid DVR-LX TX/RX ranges\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? configurations that are not technically feasible\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? configurations that may be technically feasible but not realistically licensable in the selected country\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? a quote/order-style summary that mirrors the intent of the supplemental ordering form\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 1.2 Product Principles\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 1. Accuracy before convenience.\par
\pard\sa120 The app must never imply that a technically valid frequency plan is automatically licensable.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 2. Explainability over black-box output.\par
\pard\sa120 Every result must show why a plan passed or failed: band window, spacing rule, passband rule, pairing rule, or regulatory policy rule.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 3. Regulatory humility.\par
\pard\sa120 The app is a planning aid, not legal advice and not a replacement for FCC/ISED coordination, APCO/IMS A, or Motorola Solutions review.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 4. Vendor-faithful logic.\par
\pard\sa120 Technical plan evaluation must follow the Motorola Solutions ordering guide and in-band-operation guidance first, then layer country-specific regulatory checks on top.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 5. Modular rules engine.\par
\pard\sa120 Technical validation and regulatory validation must be separate modules so rules can evolve independently.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 6. Ordering-guide fixed ranges first.\par
\pard\sa120 When the Motorola Solutions ordering guide lists fixed DVRS TX/RX ranges for a standard plan, those published ranges control the plan definition. The app should recommend the feasible DVRS sub-range inside the published plan range that satisfies the plan rules. Technical validity for that plan means at least one paired DVRS channel inside the published fixed range can satisfy the plan rules.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 7. Return the surviving compliant sub-range.\par
\pard\sa120 For every plan, whether it uses a fixed ordering-guide range or only a broader allowed window, the engine must search for the remaining paired DVRS sub-range that still satisfies that plan's spacing, window, and pairing rules. If the nominal DVRS window is close to, partially overlaps, or would otherwise conflict with the system frequencies, the app must shrink the recommendation to the surviving compliant sub-range instead of rejecting the plan solely because the full nominal range would not fit. Reject the plan only when no compliant paired sub-range remains.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 8. Conservative classification.\par
\pard\sa120 When the app cannot determine licensability with high confidence, it must say "coordination required" rather than "valid."\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 9. Ordering workflow alignment.\par
\pard\sa120 The final output must look usable by radio technicians and procurement staff, not just developers.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 1.3 Scope\b0\par
\pard\sa120 In scope:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Motorola Solutions DVR-LX standard 700 MHz and 800 MHz in-band configurations\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? country toggle for `United States` and `Canada`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? user input of the system frequency ranges actually available to the customer\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? explicit system-frequency configuration selection: `700 only`, `800 only`, or `700 and 800`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? inferred 700 MHz / 800 MHz system-band detection where possible for single-band entries\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? mixed 700 MHz and 800 MHz system evaluation\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? computed system TX/RX summary\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? proposed DVRS TX/RX ranges for each standard plan\par
\pard\sa120   For fixed-range plans, these should be the recommended feasible sub-range inside the ordering-guide plan range, not a range that overlaps the system frequencies in violation of the plan spacing rules.\par
\pard\sa120   For all plans, if only part of the nominal DVRS range remains spacing-compliant, return that surviving compliant sub-range rather than failing the plan.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? final-entry fields for actual licensed DVRS frequencies\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? plan-by-plan feasibility and regulatory status\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Out of scope for v1:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? VHF technical plan support\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? UHF technical plan support\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? direct FCC ULS or ISED license lookups\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? automatic frequency coordination\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? custom Motorola Solutions filtering plans\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? cross-band configuration recommendation as the main output\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? final legal certification that a channel is assignable\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 1.4 Output States\b0\par
\pard\sa120 Each configuration must end in one of these states:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Technically valid + regulatorily plausible`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Technically valid + coordination required`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Technically invalid`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Technically valid but outside likely public-safety band plan`\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa160\sb120\b\fs26 2. Specification\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 2.1 Source Constraints Taken From the Attached PDFs\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 The app must encode the following Motorola Solutions guidance:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Only standard frequency plans are standard offerings; anything else is custom.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? In-band filters are mechanically tuned and cannot be re-tuned in the field.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? In-band MSU transmit power must not exceed 50 W in DVRS-enabled modes.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? 700/800 in-band plans use a maximum DVR-LX passband of 1 MHz in the 2019 guidance, while the newer ordering guide expands certain 800 MHz plan windows; the rules engine should version the plan definitions explicitly and default to the latest ordering guide used by the project.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? The supplemental-ordering-form layout is the right model for the final summary panel.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 2.2 User Inputs\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Required inputs:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Country`: `United States` or `Canada`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `System frequency configuration`\par
\pard\sa120   - `700 only`\par
\pard\sa120   - `800 only`\par
\pard\sa120   - `700 and 800`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? For `700 only`\par
\pard\sa120   - `700 MHz system frequency low (MHz)`\par
\pard\sa120   - `700 MHz system frequency high (MHz)`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? For `800 only`\par
\pard\sa120   - `800 MHz system frequency low (MHz)`\par
\pard\sa120   - `800 MHz system frequency high (MHz)`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? For `700 and 800`\par
\pard\sa120   - `700 MHz system frequency low/high (MHz)`\par
\pard\sa120   - `800 MHz system frequency low/high (MHz)`\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Derived inputs:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? detected system-band family\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? detected entered system passband\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? paired system TX range, where the offset is deterministic for 700 MHz and 800 MHz system models\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Terminology rule:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? The system frequency inputs describe the frequencies already present in the customer system.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Standard plan names such as `700-A`, `700-B`, `700-C`, `800-A1`, `800-A2`, `800-B`, and `800-C` are named for the DVRS band placement, not the system band.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Because of that, a `700` plan may be evaluated against an `800 only` system model, and an `800` plan may be evaluated against a `700 only` system model, when the standard plan definition allows it.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Conditional inputs:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Manual mobile receive override`\par
\pard\sa120 Use only when the project later expands beyond deterministic 700 MHz and 800 MHz pairing rules.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Optional inputs:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Use latest ordering-guide ruleset` toggle, default `true`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Agency notes`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Actual licensed DVRS low/high TX`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `Actual licensed DVRS low/high RX`\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 2.3 System-Frequency Configuration And Band Detection\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 The UI should ask the user which system frequencies they have, not which plan family they want.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 The app should interpret the provided system-frequency inputs as follows:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `700 only`\par
\pard\sa120   - one entered range in `799-805 MHz`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `800 only`\par
\pard\sa120   - one entered range in `806-824 MHz`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `700 and 800`\par
\pard\sa120   - one entered `700 MHz` system range and one entered `800 MHz` system range\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 For single-band entries, the app should infer the system band family from the entered system range:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `700 MHz`: 799-805 MHz system frequencies\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `800 MHz`: 806-824 MHz system frequencies\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 If the input falls outside the supported 700 MHz or 800 MHz windows, the app must stop and show an input error.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 2.4 System Frequency Computation\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 The app must compute and display:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `System RX` = the entered system frequency range\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `System TX` = paired system transmit range inferred from the applicable deterministic system model\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Deterministic defaults:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `700 MHz system`: system TX = entered system RX - 30 MHz\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `800 MHz system`: system TX = entered system RX + 45 MHz\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `700 and 800 mixed systems`: plan evaluation must use the band-specific system range attached to each candidate plan, and any returned DVRS recommendation must be computed from that same candidate plan's band-specific system ranges\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 2.5 Technical Plan Engine\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Represent each standard in-band configuration as data, not hard-coded UI logic.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Each plan definition should contain:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `id`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `bandFamily`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `displayName`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `mountCompatibility`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `dvrsTxWindow`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `dvrsRxWindow`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `requiredDvrsSpacing`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `requiredMsuSpacing`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `minSeparationRules`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `maxDvrsPassband`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `maxMsuPassband`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `fixedDvrsTxRange`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `fixedDvrsRxRange`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `notes`\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Planned standard in-band coverage for v1:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? 700 MHz: Plans `A`, `B`, `C`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? 800 MHz: Plans `A1`, `A2`, `B`, `C`\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Parent-plan evaluation model:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? The UI must present only parent plans.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Some parent plans internally evaluate multiple system-frequency submodels.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? A parent plan passes if any supported submodel passes.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? The selected parent result returned to the UI must preserve the system ranges used by the winning submodel.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Required system-model mappings:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? For `800 only` system input, evaluate:\par
\pard\sa120   - `700-A`\par
\pard\sa120   - `700-B` using the `800 only` submodel\par
\pard\sa120   - `700-C` using the `800 only` submodel\par
\pard\sa120   - `800-C`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? For `700 only` system input, evaluate:\par
\pard\sa120   - `700-B` using the `700 only` submodel\par
\pard\sa120   - `700-C` using the `700 only` submodel\par
\pard\sa120   - `800-A1` using the `700 only` submodel\par
\pard\sa120   - `800-A2` using the `700 only` submodel\par
\pard\sa120   - `800-B` using the `700 only` submodel\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? For `700 and 800` system input, evaluate:\par
\pard\sa120   - `700-B`\par
\pard\sa120   - `700-C`\par
\pard\sa120   - `800-A1`\par
\pard\sa120   - `800-A2`\par
\pard\sa120   - `800-B`\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 For each plan, evaluate:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 1. Does the selected system-frequency model map to a supported submodel for the parent plan?\par
\pard\sa120 2. Does the relevant system RX/TX block fit the plan's allowed windows?\par
\pard\sa120 3. If the ordering guide provides fixed DVRS TX/RX ranges for that plan, use those fixed ranges as the plan boundary and compute the recommended feasible DVRS sub-range inside that published plan range.\par
\pard\sa120 4. For fixed-range plans, determine whether at least one paired DVRS channel inside the published fixed range satisfies the spacing, window, and pairing rules.\par
\pard\sa120 5. For non-fixed plans, search the allowed windows for the surviving paired DVRS sub-range that satisfies the spacing, window, and pairing rules.\par
\pard\sa120 6. The proposed DVRS TX/RX ranges returned to the user must themselves satisfy the selected plan's required separations, even if that means returning only a narrow slice of the nominal plan range.\par
\pard\sa120 7. Near-adjacency or partial overlap between the nominal DVRS range and the system range is not by itself a reason to fail a plan; fail only if no compliant paired DVRS sub-range remains after applying the plan rules.\par
\pard\sa120 8. Is required channel spacing or duplex split respected?\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Return:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? boolean pass/fail\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? list of failures\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? resulting proposed DVRS TX range\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? resulting proposed DVRS RX range\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 2.6 Regulatory Rules Engine\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 The regulatory engine must be a second pass applied after technical evaluation.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Each result gets:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `regulatoryStatus`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `confidence`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `reasonCodes`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `humanSummary`\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Recommended statuses:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `LIKELY_LICENSABLE`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `COORDINATION_REQUIRED`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `LIKELY_NOT_LICENSABLE`\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 #### United States rules for v1\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Use a conservative model:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `700 MHz`: treat 769-775 / 799-805 as public-safety-capable.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `800 MHz`: treat public-safety use as plausible within the 800 public-safety pool and interoperability structure, but note border-area and channel-category constraints.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 #### Canada rules for v1\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 Use a similarly conservative model:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `768-776 / 798-806 MHz`: treat as public-safety-capable.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `821-824 / 866-869 MHz`: treat as specifically public-safety-capable in 800 MHz.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? `806-821 / 851-866 MHz`: treat as broader land-mobile spectrum that may be used depending on sub-allocation and coordination; mark coordination-required unless a later ruleset refines it by channel block.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 2.7 Result Presentation\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 The app should render three panes:\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 1. `Input + System Summary`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? country\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? selected system-frequency configuration\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? detected system band\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? user-entered system frequency low/high, or both entered 700 and 800 system ranges\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? computed or assumed system TX low/high\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? warnings about assumptions\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 2. `Standard Configuration Matrix`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? one card or row per standard in-band plan\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? technical status\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? regulatory status\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? valid proposed DVRS TX range\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? valid proposed DVRS RX range\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? concise reason text\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 3. `Ordering Form Summary`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? system TX/RX values\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? proposed DVRS TX/RX range\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? blank editable fields for actual licensed DVRS TX/RX\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? notes area\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? export-friendly layout\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 2.8 UX Requirements\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Do not hide rejected plans; show all standard plans for the detected band family.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Use color plus text labels; color alone is not enough.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Every failed plan must expose the exact failing rule.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Every yellow/red regulatory status must show a disclaimer and source basis.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Show the Motorola Solutions note that custom plans require vendor review.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120\sb80\b 2.9 Non-Functional Requirements\b0\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Rules must be data-driven JSON or TypeScript objects.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Regulatory rules must be versioned separately from technical plan rules.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? Every calculation should be unit-tested.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80 ? App should support future addition of `VHF`, `UHF`, `federal`, `rail`, or `utility` profiles without rewriting the core engine.\par
\pard\sa120\par
