\pard\sa160\sb120\b\fs26 5. Important Assumptions\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\sa120 1. The app should prefer the more recent ordering guide logic when the older narrative document and newer ordering guide differ.\par
\pard\sa120    When the ordering guide publishes fixed standard-plan DVRS ranges, those ranges define the allowed recommendation boundary, while the returned proposed DVRS ranges must be a spacing-compliant subset when overlap would otherwise occur.\par
\pard\sa120    The same subset-selection principle applies to non-fixed plans inside their broader allowed windows.\par
\pard\sa120 2. The app should target typical state, provincial, county, municipal, and agency public-safety users, not federal-only licensing profiles, in v1.\par
\pard\sa120 3. The app should classify uncertain licensability as `coordination required`.\par
\pard\sa120 4. The app should preserve a data model flexible enough to add VHF and UHF planning later, even though v1 only evaluates 700 MHz and 800 MHz plans.\par
\pard\sa120\par
